back to us anyway?

24:33.013 --> 24:34.764
Because when I bought it,
I signed Randy Lahey.

24:34.848 --> 24:35.932
-[chuckle]
-Nice.

24:36.183 --> 24:38.602
I think we did it, boys.
We're in the fucking clear.

24:39.019 --> 24:40.145
I fucking hope so...

24:40.228 --> 24:42.189
-Just wait! Listen!
-[dog barking]

24:42.272 --> 24:44.024
Oh, the fucking K9 unit!

24:44.107 --> 24:46.026
-All right, let's run!
-K9 unit!

24:46.109 --> 24:47.068
God damn it!

24:47.444 --> 24:48.612
[Bubbles whimpering]

24:48.904 --> 24:51.072
[Ricky] I forgot how fun it is
running from the cops!

24:51.156 --> 24:54.367
[Bubbles] Oh yeah,
this is a fucking treat, Ricky!

24:54.451 --> 24:56.161
Just a fucking treat!

24:59.456 --> 25:00.790
I fucking love you guys.

25:00.874 --> 25:02.250
Get the fuck in the truck!

25:02.334 --> 25:03.919
-Thank God for country people...
-[Julian] Get in!

25:04.002 --> 25:05.503
...leaving their fucking keys
in their vehicles.

25:05.587 --> 25:06.880
[Bubbles] Are we just taking a truck?

25:06.963 --> 25:08.632
-[Ricky] We're just fucking taking it.
-[dogs barking]

25:08.715 --> 25:10.717
-[engine ignition]
-[Bubbles] Let's just go, Ricky.

25:10.800 --> 25:14.095
-Hey, fuckers!
-[overlapping yelling, gunshot]

25:14.346 --> 25:16.014
[Bubbles] Jesus Christ, fuck!

25:16.598 --> 25:17.807
[Julian] Everybody okay?

25:18.225 --> 25:19.976
I hope to fuck they're still here.

25:20.852 --> 25:22.479
There he is.
Fuck.

25:22.979 --> 25:25.273
[Bubbles] Let's just get this
fucking over with, boys.

25:25.857 --> 25:27.317
Oh, my God.

25:28.235 --> 25:29.903
[Ricky] It's almost done, Bubs.

25:31.112 --> 25:33.490
[Tommy] Oh, look who decides
to show up.

25:33.823 --> 25:36.660
Who the fuck do you guys think you are,
making us wait out here

25:36.743 --> 25:39.412
for over a goddamn hour?
Fuck you, fuck you and fuck you!

25:39.496 --> 25:42.499
-That's it, the deal is off!
-[mixed yelling, guns clicking]

25:42.874 --> 25:45.835
You can't even imagine what the fuck
we just went through to get here!

25:45.919 --> 25:48.505
We've got the 'shrooms.
Give us our fucking cash!

25:49.089 --> 25:52.008
Guys, guys... relax.

25:52.092 --> 25:55.512
-I'm just fucking around with you.
-[Bubbles] Jesus Christ, cold play!

25:55.595 --> 25:58.848
-Yeah, you almost got fucking shot.
-All right, come on, guys.

25:58.932 --> 26:01.601
Let's do this motherfucking deal, huh?

26:01.685 --> 26:03.812
I'm gonna need you to
shut that fucking shit down

26:03.895 --> 26:05.397
right the fuck now.

26:06.147 --> 26:08.608
You heard him, snail muff.
Shut the fucking cameras down!

26:09.609 --> 26:10.986
[meowing]

26:11.069 --> 26:12.779
[Ricky] Holy fuck I was hungry.

26:13.071 --> 26:15.198
Here, boys. These are
as cold as a whore's heart.

26:15.282 --> 26:16.324
-Yeah!
-Thanks, buddy.

26:16.408 --> 26:17.534
This had to be

26:17.617 --> 26:20.036
the most fucked up,
scariest day of my life.

26:20.120 --> 26:22.289
I hear you.
But was it fucking worth it, though?

26:23.915 --> 26:25.750
-Yes.
-[laughter]

26:25.834 --> 26:27.210
-There you go!
-Boys, you realize

26:27.294 --> 26:29.004
this is the first time in history

26:29.087 --> 26:31.047
that we've pulled off
a job this successfully?

26:31.131 --> 26:32.674
-No, it's not.
-Ever. It is, Ricky.

26:32.757 --> 26:34.301
Now, knock on wood, everybody.

26:34.384 --> 26:36.094
[Julian] Finally.
I mean, it was a bit risky.

26:36.177 --> 26:37.721
It was pretty dumb but, boys,

26:37.804 --> 26:39.931
our future's looking
pretty fucking bright right now.

26:40.015 --> 26:41.016
Really fucking bright.

26:41.099 --> 26:43.143
Corey Hart couldn't look
at our future, baby.

26:43.226 --> 26:44.060
Here we fucking go!

26:44.144 --> 26:46.771
I don't think so! What do you
want? Get the fuck out of here!

26:46.855 --> 26:49.149
Tell that dick-twisted George Green
to leave me the fuck alone.

26:49.232 --> 26:50.859
He called the cops on me
for nothing!

26:50.942 --> 26:53.236
-Calm the frig down, Ricky.
-No! I'm not calming the frig down.

26:53.320 --> 26:55.905
-Fuck you!
-Mr. Lahey fired George.

26:55.989 --> 26:57.490
-What?
-We come in peace.

26:58.658 --> 26:59.617
Julian...

27:01.328 --> 27:03.038
I'd like to take this opportunity

27:03.121 --> 27:04.622
to wipe the slate clean, Julian.

27:04.706 --> 27:06.499
Oh, yeah?
How you gonna do that now?

27:06.583 --> 27:07.542
Julian,

27:08.293 --> 27:09.544
I'm gonna tell you something.

27:09.627 --> 27:11.046
And after I finish telling you,

27:11.129 --> 27:13.131
you're probably gonna wanna
beat the shit out of me.

27:13.214 --> 27:16.051
But it's a shit weight
I need to have lifted off my shoulders.

27:16.134 --> 27:18.011
-Mr. Lahey, are you sure...
-Randy.

27:19.387 --> 27:20.263
Randy...

27:20.889 --> 27:23.641
Randy and I...

27:23.725 --> 27:27.354
we had $25,000
we were gonna give to you, Julian,

27:27.437 --> 27:30.398
and honest...
But I lost it at the racetrack.

27:30.482 --> 27:33.193
You lost 25 grand at
the fucking racetrack?

27:33.276 --> 27:35.820
-Are you fucking kidding me?
-[overlapping conversation]

27:35.904 --> 27:38.198
-I was drunk, Julian. I was drunk!
-Julian, just...

27:38.281 --> 27:40.575
-take a deep breath.
-Now we have nothing, Julian.

27:40.658 --> 27:42.702
[slurring] We're totally broke.
If I ever... money,

27:42.786 --> 27:44.704
I would give it to you.
All of you, Julian.

27:44.788 --> 27:46.539
I'm sorry, so...
You can...

27:46.623 --> 27:48.541
pound the shit out of me
if you want to,

27:48.625 --> 27:52.003
but please don't fucking let Ricky
come every fucking day

27:52.087 --> 27:54.964
for the rest of our lives and
wreck our fucking trailer!

27:55.048 --> 27:57.133
-Okay, Julian...
-We'll fucking see, won't we?

27:57.217 --> 28:00.053
Take a deep breath, Julian.
Think hard about this.

28:00.136 --> 28:03.098
You think about the future that
we were just talking about.

28:03.348 --> 28:05.266
And if you hold him down
and pound on him,

28:05.350 --> 28:07.018
what's that going to accomplish?

28:07.102 --> 28:09.104
Nothing. Think.
Use your brains.

28:09.479 --> 28:11.856
What are you talking about,
pounding?

28:11.940 --> 28:14.025
It took a lot of balls
to tell me the truth.

28:14.109 --> 28:15.902
-Thank you, I appreciate it.
-There you go.

28:15.985 --> 28:17.570
-Let it out.
-You know what?

28:17.904 --> 28:19.864
We're all getting too old
for this bullshit,

28:19.948 --> 28:20.990
-okay?
-Yeah.

28:21.074 --> 28:23.076
And our lives are
finally coming together,

28:23.410 --> 28:25.328
and I'm getting married
for fuck's sakes.

28:25.412 --> 28:27.038
-There we go.
-Congratulations, Julian.

28:27.122 --> 28:28.498
-So, it's like...
-Look, just... Julian...

28:28.581 --> 28:30.041
I think what he's trying to say...

28:30.125 --> 28:32.919
and I speak for all three of us.
Boys...

28:33.586 --> 28:34.587
I do.

28:34.838 --> 28:38.466
We are willing to let
the past be the past.

28:38.925 --> 28:40.385
-Yeah?
-Right?

28:40.719 --> 28:41.636
That's great.

28:41.720 --> 28:43.304
-Right.
-Yeah, okay.

28:43.388 --> 28:45.056
For the future.

28:45.140 --> 28:47.642
-That's very gracious of you, guys.
-[clinking]

28:47.726 --> 28:50.520
-And, uh, I think I can speak for the...
-Ran...

28:51.146 --> 28:53.940
-Ran.
-Thanks, Mr. Lahey.

28:54.023 --> 28:57.485
As I was saying, I think I can speak
for the two of us too,

28:57.819 --> 29:00.447
and we agree,
the past is the past.

29:00.780 --> 29:03.992
Yeah, that's what I just said, Randy,
but good try, bud.

29:04.451 --> 29:06.661
-This is very exciting!
-Yeah!

29:06.745 --> 29:08.621
-A new era.
-[chuckling]

29:09.205 --> 29:10.206
Okay.

29:10.790 --> 29:11.666
[sobbing]

29:11.750 --> 29:14.669
-All right, you're sweaty, you smell.
